Chorioamnionitis: maternal fever greater than 38; may also have maternal white blood cell count greater than 15, foul smelling discharge or fetal tachycardia. Maternal rupture of membranes greater than 18 hours. Premature delivery may be due to maternal infection.

column2: Delivery Note-Liveborn APGAR score at 1 minute
column3:
Apgar Scoring System (Based on 0 Points, 1 Point and 2 Points system)<li><li><li>
A (Activity)<li>
0 Points=Absent,       
1 Point=Flexed arms and legs,
2 Points=Active<li>P (Pulse)<li>
0 Points=Absent,        
1 Point=below 100 bpm,
2 Points=Over 100 bpm<li><li>G (Grimace)<li>
0 Points=Floopy, 1 Point=Minimal Response to stimulation, 2 Points=Prompt response to stimulation<li><li>
A (Appearance)<li>
0 Points=Blue;Pale, 1 Point=pink body, blue extremities, 2 Points=Pink<li>
R (Respiration) <li>
0 Points=Absent, 1 Point=Slow and irregular, 2 Points=Vigorous cry
